Wii Optical Disc FS
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Mount your Wii disc images on a local directory using the FUSE API.

1. How to use
=============

$ ./wodmount --help

You can also install wodmount on your system using distutils:

$ python2 setup.py install

2. Dependencies
===============

* PyCrypto (needed for AES computations)
* PyFS (used to expose the FS with FUSE)

3. Use the wod library
======================

wod is also a Python 2.x package you can use in your applications. There are
several layers you can use, from the lowest level to the highest level:

* wod.disc: disc image access, partition table, game metadata.
* wod.partition: crypted partition access, DOL/bootloader/FS raw access.
* wod.wodfs: "high level" API to access files on WOD partitions.
* wod.fs: a PyFS filesystem using wod.wodfs. Recommanded for most usages.

